<font color="#4682b4" size="4" face="Arial"> <i>Supported Operations:
</i></font>

<p>The Equation Editor supports the following:</p>
<ul>
<li> <i>Basic arithmetic operations:</i>  addition, subtraction, multiplication, division; 
<li> <i>Relational operations:</i> less than, greater than, less then or equal to, greater than or equal to, not equal;
<li> <i>Logical operations:</i> and, or, not;
<li><i>Other arithmetic operations:</i> absolute value, remainder.
<li><i>Trigonometric operations: </i>sin, cos, tan; 
</ul>

<i>User Defined Functions</i> are supported in the form of: 
<p><center><i>functionName </i>(Object name, time) </center></p>
where Object name refers to the object on the Stage currently dealt with (ME) or any other object in relation with the it (OTEHR1, OTHER2, …, OTHER9).  
The functions are functions of time and the second argument specifies  particular time instance.  
</p>


